<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Holds News Conference on Sarajevo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702213894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 2142 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702213894 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Sarajevo, 7 Feb (TANJUG) -- At a news conference 
in Sarajevo today, Srpska republic president Radovan Karadzic 
described the U.S. Administration's request that Saturday's 
crime at a Sarajevo market be investigated as "based on 
principles." [passage omitted] 
  Commenting on the talks yesterday with Akashi, Stoltenberg, 
and Owen, Karadzic said that a draft agreement on placing 
Sarajevo under a UN protectorate and on putting an end to the 
fighting in the area had been a good idea, but that it had never 
been signed due to the behavior of the Muslim side. 
  "We are ready to revive this issue in Geneva on 10 February 
in order to reach a partial peace, since the solution of the 
Sarajevo issue would lead to the resolution of the conflict in 
other areas of Bosnia-Herzegovina too," Karadzic said. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

