<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Krajisnik Rejects Serb Responsibility </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702151694 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0702151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview for a Netherlands daily, DE 
VOLKSKRAND, Momcilo Krajisnik, president of the Assembly of the 
Srpska republic, spoke, among other things, about the massacre 
that took place in Sarajevo on Saturday [5 February]. 
  [Begin Krajisnik recording] We do not have any information 
at present. The only thing that we know is that the Serbian 
side did not do it. However, we have some indications, 
suspicions, that there is even a possibility of this having been 
committed by a third side, neither the Serbian nor the Muslim 
side, but a side that does not want an agreement to be reached 
between the Muslims and the Serbs. We had been on a very good 
way to signing a document similar to the document and the 
statement signed between the Serbs and the Croats, and just at 
the time of this rapprochement, we found ourselves in the 
situation of these talks being undermined. We cannot say what 
forces these are. There are too many interested parties that 
would want the war to continue here and that do not want 
rapprochement between the Muslims and the Serbs. [end recoding] 

</TEXT>

