<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explains Resignation Decision </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802140894 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mate Boban, president of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna, placed the office of president at the disposal of 
the assembly until further notice at an extraordinary session of 
the chamber of deputies of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. 
  [Begin Boban recording] I have decided to place the office 
of 
president of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna at the disposal 
of the assembly until further notice. My duties will be carried 
out by the presidential council which will appoint one of its 
members to represent the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna. [end 
recording] 
  Explaining his decision, Boban said that the most 
influential 
international players have been misled due to a lack of 
information and he believes that certain politicians, and not 
the will of the Croat nation, stand in the way of a 
multicultural, multiethnic, and unitary Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
This belief of the international public, which leads to growing 
pressure on the Republic of Croatia, is the reason why Boban had 
offered to resign. 
  [Begin Boban recording] I am saying this at the beginning so 
that those who believe in other interpretations in the Croat 
nation in Bosnia-Herzegovina would not describe this as a result 
of [word indistinct]. [end recording] 
  I will stay with you, Boban said at the end of his speech, 
in 
which he recalled that the will of the Croat nation in Bosnia- 
Herzegovina was defined two years ago in a referendum formulated 
in Livno, which approved Bosnia-Herzegovina, not as a unitary 
state but as one in which the Croat nation would have equal 
rights and the right to self-determination. We still support 
Bosnia-Herzegovina as a union of three republics, because we 
enabled it to survive by defending 35 percent of its territory. 
However, the Serbs and the Muslims do not want this 
Bosnia-Herzegovina anymore. 
  Boban also mentioned the meetings of self-proclaimed Croat 
assemblies and he said that this assembly is the only legitimate 
representative of the Croats' will in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

