<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croat Assembly Focuses on `Self-Determination' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802111694 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1000 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802111694 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Zdenko Vranjes] </F>
  [Excerpts] The extraordinary session of the chamber of 
deputies of the Croat republic of Herceg-Bosna began at 1000 in 
the packed hall of the People's University in Livno. Members of 
former chamber of citizens of the Bosnia-Herzegovina assembly 
are also present at the session as well as members of the 
Bosnia-Herzegovina Presidency Miro Lasic, Franjo Boras and 
Fikret Abdic. Representatives of the Catholic Church in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, municipal governments of Herceg-Bosna and 
numerous organizations of the Croat nation in Bosnia-Herzegovina 
are also present. 
  Members of the state delegation of the Republic of Croatia, 
headed by Minister of Foreign Affairs Mate Granic are also 
attending the session. [passage omitted] 
  There is only one item on the agenda: the current military 
and political situation of the Croat nation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina's struggle for its rights and survival. In 
his introductory speech, the president of the Croat republic of 
Herceg-Bosna and the Croat Democratic Community of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina, Mate Boban, recalled that two years ago the 
well-known Livno referendum question was formulated which 
rejected the unitary organization of Bosnia-Herzegovina and 
proclaimed the basic will of the Croat nation in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina: Equal rights and a right to 
self-determination. Boban said that this basic goal had not 
been abandoned. 

</TEXT>

