<H3> <TI>   Croats `Forcibly Mobilized' in Zenica </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702154994 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1400 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702154994 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A forced mobilization of Croats is being carried out 
in Zenica, the Croatian Defense Council's Zenica information 
service has reported. The Croats forcibly mobilized by the 
Muslim army are being sent to the front lines and forced to 
shoot at their dearest ones -- fathers, brothers, and sons. 
Recalcitrant Croats and those refusing to be mobilized are 
being arrested in large numbers. 
  The building housing the Croatian cultural center, which is 
a 
symbol of Croatian struggle, has been turned into a Muslim 
forces' military building. Before that it was a frequent target 
of Muslim fire. The Croatian population of Zenica is quietly 
resisting all forms of imposed Muslim authority. 

</TEXT>

