<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Croats `Still Violating' Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702131194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1237 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Knin, 7 Feb (TANJUG) -- Croatian forces are still 
violating the cease-fire in the Benkovac area on the northern 
Dalmatian battlefront. 
  The main headquarters of the Serb Krajina army has reported 
that they opened fire on the area around the village of Biljani 
Gornji from recoilless guns and howitzers. Due to the intensity 
of fire, and because the soldiers, weapons and equipment of the 
Serb side were endangered, the Serb side was forced to respond. 
A statement says that while returning fire the Serb side 
destroyed one tank and one antiaircraft gun belonging to the 
aggressor. 
  The main headquarters of the Serb Krajina army warns that 
Croatia is using the cease-fire to regroup and bring in fresh 
forces and equipment to this section of the battlefield. 

</TEXT>

