<F P=100> CROATIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Valentic, Drnovsek Sign Agreements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702141494 Zagreb Radio Croatia Network in Serbo-Croatian 
1200 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Zagreb Radio Croatia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The prime ministers of the Republics of Croatia and 
Slovenia, Nikica Valentic and Janez Drnovsek respectively, 
signed in Zagreb six agreements on cooperation in various 
fields. Intensive talks over the past few weeks resulted in the 
regulation of future relations between the two countries in the 
sphere of education, culture, employement, and judiciary, 
cooperation in sea fishing, and economic and trade relations. 
  Ater the talks between the two prime ministers and their 
associates and after the agreements were signed in Banski Dvori 
in Zagreb, both prime ministers expressed satisfaction with the 
progress made in relations between the two countries. According 
to them, today's talks are the result of several months of hard 
work and meetings between experts and state officials. At the 
same time, the talks are an added impetus for solving the 
remaining problems. Both also said that there are no disputed 
issues or unsolvable problems beween the two countries. 
  The Croatian prime minister also said that it was 
understandable that both countries were interested in 
cooperation because we are encouraged to cooperate by tradition 
and other interests. Slovene Prime Minister Janez Drnovsek 
added that both countries would benefit from more intense 
cooperation, especially in the field of economy. 

</TEXT>

