Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Several SdRP [Social Democracy of the Polish 
Republic] politicians holding high government offices met this 
evening at party headquarters. There will be no comment; it was 
an informal meeting of several SLD [Democratic Left Alliance] 
ministers, the Social Democracy press spokesman, Zbigniew 
Siemiatkowski, said after the meeting. 
  He also stated that the SLD would adopt a position on the 
prime minister's acceptance of Marek Borowski's resignation only 
after today's [8 February] meeting of the coalition. 
  The spokesman also denied a report by REUTERS that SdRP 
leader Aleksander Kwasniewski has a candidate for finance 
minister. 

