<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agriculture Group Demands Government Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802115194 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1000 
GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The national protest committee for the defense of 
Polish agriculture has asked the highest authorities of Poland 
to start talks urgently. Andrzej Lepper, the leader of the 
Samoobrona [militant farmers organization], suggested a state 
farm at Montowo in Torun Province as the venue for talks. 
  The committee demands, among other things, the increase of 
funds for agriculture by 8 trillion zlotys by raising the budget 
deficit, and that priority be given to workers' companies in 
leasing former state farms. It also demands cheap credits for 
the purchase of turnover assets and for running production, and 
that those guilty of destroying Polish agriculture be called to 
account. 

</TEXT>

