<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Denounces Sarajevo Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802145494 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802145494 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 1100 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Slovak 
Republic today issued a statement on the criminal attack on the 
Sarajevo market. In its statement, the ministry strongly 
denounces such deliberate attacks, whichever of the fighting 
sides is their originator. 
  At the same time, the Foreign Ministry appeals to the UN 
secretary general and the UN Security Council to adopt more 
radical measures to speed up the solution to the situation on 
the territory of Bosnia-Herzegovina, which is becoming 
unbearable both politically and from the humanitarian point of 
view. 
  The Slovak Republic will continue to assist in the search 
for 
a peaceful solution to the war conflict on the entire territory 
of the former Yugoslavia in accordance with the extent of its 
possibilities, says the statement issued by the Foreign Ministry. 

</TEXT>

