<H3> <TI>   Organizations Warn Against NATO Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0702135494 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1209 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0702135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 7 Feb (TANJUG) -- The White Rose and the 
New Byzantium-Orthodox Concord today warned the NATO Council 
that if Bosnian Serbs positions were attacked, these 
nongovernmental organizations would mount a "complete and total" 
blockade of the Danube "for a one-year period." 
  It is noted in a statement signed by Radomir Smiljanic, 
president of the White Rose and of the Danube Blockade Council, 
that "we all genuinely and deeply mourn the innocent victims of 
Sarajevo, but at the same time we wish to draw attention to the 
fact that for the fourth time the unscrupulous propaganda 
machine of the Bosnian Muslim government and world agents have 
used the same trick." 
  "The suffering of the innocent is used to move the world 
public and NATO's military power against the Serbs and to 
undermine the Geneva peace process," the statement says and goes 
on to warn the NATO Council "under no circumstances to take 
military action or mount air strikes against the Serbs in former 
Bosnia-Herzegovina." 

</TEXT>

