<F P=101> Macedonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party of Serbs Demands Constitutional Recognition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702163194 Skopje MILS-NEWS in English 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Skopje MILS-NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Serbs Must Be Included in the </F>
Constitution"] 
  [Text] The newly appointed leadership of the Democratic 
Party of the Serbs in Macedonia (DPS) denies the report signed 
by the party's ex-president Boro Ristic and by the Macedonian 
Internal Minister Ljubomir Frckovski, saying the Serbian people 
does not accept that signature. For the new DPS leader, Dragisa 
Miletic, the way chosen by the Serbian people is much more 
agreeable -- they demand an explicit constitutional recognition 
of the Serbs, as a guarantee of their equal rights with all 
other minorities in Macedonia. In other words, the Macedonian 
Government is to include the Serbs in its official list of 
minorities in the country, in 18 months. Otherwise, the next 
step of DPS will be raising of the Serbian question in Macedonia 
in front of international institutions, Miletic said. 

</TEXT>

