<H3> <TI>   Draskovic Elected Head of DEPOS Group </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802154394 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1055 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802154394 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Belgrade, 8 Feb (TANJUG) -- Vuk Draskovic has been 
elected head of the Democratic Movement of Serbia [DEPOS] 
deputies group in the Serbian parliament. The DEPOS group has 
45 deputies and is the second largest after the Socialists. 

</TEXT>

