<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Karadzic Addresses Clinton, Yeltsin on Market </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0802195094 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 1830 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0802195094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In a letter today Radovan Karadzic, president of 
the republic of Srpska, informed U.S. and Russian Presidents 
Bill Clinton and Boris Yeltsin that a great and feeble deception 
took place at the Sarajevo market. Accepting full 
responsibility for every word in the letter, Karadzic emphasizes 
that an explosion in which few people were killed and injured 
took place at the market, while everything else surrounding this 
incident was stage-managed. 
  There were very few goods in the market, and those were in 
only a few stalls. Eyewitnesses did not observe over 300 people 
at the market directly prior to the explosion, but only a 
handful. It would not even be logical for more than 300 people 
to be present at a small market that was lacking in goods. 
  Karadzic also pointed to a very indicative fact: The Muslim 
side rejected an investigation that would be carried out by the 
UN experts with the participation of Serbian and Muslim experts. 
Interviews with survivors, as well as pathological findings on 
the causes and times of deaths, would have revealed the entire 
fake. Namely, all the witnesses, even the Muslims in the Muslim 
media, have stated that this was an unusual bomb because the 
characteristic whistling noise was not heard prior to the 
explosion. 
  Karadzic, among other things, warns that the television 
footage clearly shows that manipulation with bodies has taken 
place in this tragedy. As he says, in the footage one can see 
the bodies of casualties who had died hours earlier as well as 
plastic body parts. We must not allow, Karadzic says, that one 
warring side would deceive the entire international community, 
including the most important forces -- the United States and 
Russia, and their presidents -- and lead them to false 
conclusions. This is a great shame, he says. 
  Karadzic appealed to Clinton and Yeltsin: We beg you to 
discover the real truth by all means available to your powerful 
countries. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
