<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bosnian Serbs: `Foreign Intelligence' Involved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802155094 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1502 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0802155094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["Pool" item] </F>
  [Text] Sekovici, Feb 8 (TANJUG) -- The Serb side has 
information that the Sarajevo market massacre, which killed 68 
people, was planned by the Moslem authorities and that directly 
involved was a foreign intelligence service, TANJUG learned on 
Tuesday from reliable sources in the Bosnian Serb Republic (RS). 
  The RS sources said that the scenario and its media support 
were developped in mid-January with the participation of a group 
of Moslems from former Bosnia-Herzegovina who are active in the 
Islamic lobby in the United States. The preparations included 
three military advisors to the Moslem army who carefully planned 
the time and place of the massacre. 
  The bloodshed at the Sarajevo market was caused by a mortar 
shell and several explosive devices, but the Serb side does not 
yet have all the necessary facts. 
  The RS sources claim that there is no doubt that many 
traces, 
which would immediately show that the incident was 
stage-managed, were removed with lightening speed. 
  They said that the expertise carried out by the U.N. 
Protection Forces (UNPROFOR) was superficial and underscored the 
significance of the fact that the Moslems refused to agree that 
Serb experts take part in the investigation. 
  The RS sources said that the criminal action aimed to create 
a reason for the continuation of the pressure against the 
Bosnian Serbs, to provoke NATO air strikes and support the 
Moslem side in its aspirations to control the entire Bosnian 
territory. 
  The sources said that the stage-managed action is also an 
attempt to bring about the failure of the Geneva peace talks and 
to provide a justification to the Moslem side not to sign the 
peace plan. 
  All this is supported by the fact that Moslem Presidency 
Vice-President Ejup Ganic on Monday revealed a new Moslem 
proposal to create a cantonal Bosnia. 
  The Bosnian Serb sources learned that a new stage-managed 
action is planned in case the Sarajevo incident fails to achieve 
the wanted results, thus confirming the determination to realize 
these aims. The sources said that Moslem ambassador in the 
United Nations, Muhamed Secirbegovic, on Monday openly 
threatened to do this. If NATO fails to carry out the sir 
strikes "such incidents will recur," he said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

