<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kwasniewski: Little Chance of an Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802231094 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 2000 GMT 8 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802231094 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TV Polonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Panorama" program] </F>
  [Text] There is little chance of an accord, Aleksander 
Kwasniewski, leader of the Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] said 
after meeting with Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak and before 
talks between the SLD and the Polish Peasant Party (PSL). The 
coalition politicians met at the government hotel at Parkowa 
Street in Warsaw. Wojciech Nomejko reports: 
  [Nomejko] The coalition meeting was preceded by a private 
talk between Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak and SLD leader 
Aleksander Kwasniewski. It took place at the office of the 
Council of Ministers and lasted for over an hour. After 1900 
[1800 GMT], coalition politicians began arriving at the URM 
hotel on Parkowa Street. Just before 2000, those gathered there 
were joined by Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak and Aleksander 
Kwasniewski. The leader of the Left said that the coalition 
still exists and that the talks will be long and difficult. 

</TEXT>

