<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   SLD Spokesman: President Gains in Crisis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902102894 Warsaw PAP in Polish 0947 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0902102894 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, 9 Feb--According to Zbigniew Siemiatkowski, 
the SLD [Democratic Left Alliance] spokesman, the last-moment 
involvement of the president in the coalition crisis proves that 
if anyone has gained anything at all by the crisis, it was the 
president. 
  "The president has immediately taken the opportunity to 
point 
to the crisis in mutual relations within the coalition and also 
to the imperfection of the constitutional solutions," 
Siemiatkowski said today on Radio ESKA. 
  According to the Alliance spokesman, "the president returned 
to his idea of a strong presidency, which proves that the 
coalition crisis had been watched closely." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-30817 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu027_p_94012" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-027 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  9 Feb 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Speaker Says Coalition Crisis Resolved </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902125594 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1105 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yesterday's agreement between the Polish Peasant 
Party [PSL] and the Democratic Left Alliance [SLD] could have 
been reached earlier, we were told by Sejm Speaker Jozef Oleksy 
today. 
  [Begin Oleksy recording] I am greatly relieved by the 
successful and final conclusion of the talks. When it comes to 
the matters that aroused speculations and various rumors outside 
the coalition, the talks have put an end to the state of an 
alleged crisis, or perhaps not even an alleged crisis. They 
have put an end to the real and existing conflict, which was 
interpreted by the mass media almost as a breakdown of the 
coalition, or as the partners parting their ways because of 
internal difficulties impossible to overcome. 
  My feeling of relief comes from the fact that the will to 
continue the strategic cooperation was firmly reiterated 
yesterday not because of the lack of an alternative but because 
all of the elements that constitute the program credo and take 
into account Poland's needs, underlining the foundations of the 
coalition, were reconfirmed. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

