<F P=102>  LD0802225594 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802225594 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At its meeting in Bratislava today, the government 
approved the draft addendum on the payments agreement between 
Slovakia and the Czech Republic and the draft agreement between 
the two countries on mutual payments of outstanding claims 
ensuing for the two republics from certain agreements following 
the end of the federation. 
  Deputy Prime Minister Sergej Kozlik said that, on the basis 
of these legislative amendments, the so-called old bloc should 
be abolished and a one-bloc clearing system of accounting should 
be introduced. According to Kozlik, there were no direct talks 
at the government session today about the Slovak budget deficit. 
  At a news conference, however, he said that the government 
had to grant 6 billion Slovak korunas from the state budget to 
commence independent activity of the National Insurance Company, 
which hugely increased the state budget revenues for January. 

