<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Predicts Republic's `Speedy End' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902101394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0803 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0902101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague (DDP/ADN)--The leader of the extreme 
right-wing Russian Liberal Democratic Party, Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, has threatened retaliatory strikes against all 
countries that participate in the bombing of Serb positions. He 
regarded air strikes against Serbian cities "just as if Russian 
cities were being bombed", Zhirinovskiy told the Prague-based 
newspaper LIDOVE NOVINY. "This would completely change Russian 
foreign policy," he said. If the bombings take place, all of 
those countries involved should be aware "that whatever they do 
to Serbian cities, the same will happen to their countries. 
Bombs will fall on the cities of those countries that bomb 
Serbian cities." 
  Zhirinovskiy confirmed that he had received an invitation 
from the extreme-right Czech Republicans. He would very much 
like to come, even though this would not be welcomed by all 
sides. Zhirinovskiy predicted that the Czech Republic would come 
to a speedy end. "Your country will be destroyed. I assure you 
that, in 10 years' time, neither Moravia nor the Sudetenland 
will exist. The Czechs will be forced to speak German, forget 
their native language, attend German churches, and polish the 
boots of German officers." 

</TEXT>

