<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mazowiecki Sees NATO Air Strikes Ending War </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802222594 Warsaw TV Polonia Network in Polish 2000 GMT 8 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802222594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw TV Polonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Passages within quotation marks are recorded] </F>
  [Text] After returning from Geneva, Tadeusz Mazowiecki said 
that the UN Human Rights Commission, on account of differences 
of opinion, has not adopted a stance on the most recent events 
in Sarajevo. 
  [Mazowiecki] "This disagreement, this impossibility to agree 
some sort of joint stance, but one that is consistently 
implemented, of course encourages agression, encourages the 
perpetration of transgressions of human rights with impunity." 
  In Mazowiecki's view, the very threat of air strikes would 
allow the war to be broken off. The leader of the Democratic 
Union does not think that NATO will decide to use force. 
  [Mazowiecki] "We are constantly having to deal with the 
situation whereby, if one thing is said in Brussels, the next 
day [pauses].... If the ministers say one thing, the next day 
the ambassadors of these same countries say something else, 
ameliorating it, changing it. This is indeed worthy of 
condemnation in this situation--the incapability of adopting a 
joint stance." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

