<H3> <TI>   Vondra Sees Air Strikes as `Extreme Measure' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0802112194 Prague CTK in English 2140 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0802112194 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague Feb 7 (CTK) -- Deputy Foreign Minister 
Alexandr Vondra said on Czech Television tonight that the Czech 
Republic would not support a decision to carry out aerial 
strikes against Serb forces surrounding Sarajevo. That would be 
an extreme measure that would not solve everything, this can 
only be done by the warring parties themselves, he added. 
  Sixty-eight Sarajevans were killed and nearly 200 injured 
when a Serb artillery shell exploded in a crowded marketplace on 
Saturday [5 February], causing NATO and United Nations diplomats 
to consider anew, now with greater likelihood, launching air 
attacks against the Serb besiegers. 

</TEXT>

