<F P=101> Czech Republic </F>
<H3> <TI>   Conditions for Issuance of Yugoslav Visas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902144694 Prague CTK in English 2056 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 8 (CTK) -- Czech nationals applying for 
visa to the Yugoslav Federal Republic (Serbia and Montenegro) 
must present a valid passport, a filled-in form, and two 
photographs, Zita Senkova, a Foreign Ministry press official, 
told CTK today. 
  The applicant must also submit a verified invitation letter 
and, in case of a tourist travel, a voucher. In case of a 
transit tour, the visa of the country of destination along with 
air or railway tickets must be shown, Senkova reported. 
  The fee for one entrance or one-way transit is $20. Two 
entrances or a double transit cost $30. Several trips or a 
multiple transit for less than three months costs $50 and under 
six months $90, Senkova said, adding that the fees are paid 
exclusively in dollars. The regulation is in force starting 
today. 

</TEXT>

