<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Defense Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   `Peace-Partnership' Plan Signed </H4>
<F P=102> AU0802173794 Budapest MTI in English 1645 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0802173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 8 February (MTI) -- Hungary and Ukraine 
are to cooperate within a peace-partnership scheme, says an 
agreement reached between the two defense ministers in Budapest 
on Tuesday [8 February]. 
  Minister of Defense Lajos Fur of Hungary and Army General 
Vitaliy Radetskyy of Ukraine, held a press conference and said 
their talks also focussed on regional partnership issues, from 
which they do not wish to exclude Russia. 
  In joint arms manufacturing, Hungary is mainly interested in 
components for aircraft, tanks, and armored vehicles. Ukraine 
hopes to use Hungarian experience in reforming its Army. This 
was the second visit of a Ukrainian minister of defense to 
Hungary within two years. 

</TEXT>

