<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Defense Minister Arrives for Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Boross, Radetskyy Discuss Security </H4>
<F P=102> AU0802182494 Budapest MTI in English 1748 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0802182494 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 8 February (MTI) -- Hungarian Prime 
Minister Peter Boross discussed East-Central European security 
and early settlement of the South Slav crisis with Ukrainian 
Defence Minister Army General Vitaliy Radetskyy in the Budapest 
parliament on Tuesday [8 February]. 
  Spokesmen said that Boross had outlined the serious trade 
losses caused to Hungary from UN sanctions on rump Yugoslavia, 
and voiced concern over the fate of ethnic Hungarians in 
Vojvodina. Hungary hopes for help from Ukraine in peacefully 
settling the south Slav conflict, the prime minister added. 
  Radetskyy noted Ukraine would increase its peace-keeping 
force in Bosnia under a parliamentary decision. 
  Boross said why Hungary wants closer links with NATO, and 
stressed the importance of the peace-partnership plan. Both 
Boross and Radetskyy hoped for greater business links based on 
mutual advantages. 

</TEXT>

