<F P=101> Hungary </F>
<H3> <TI>   Assembly Elects National Electoral Committee </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902082694 Budapest MTI in English 1956 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902082694 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest MTI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Budapest, 8 February (MTI) -- Preparing for general 
elections on May 8, deputies today elected the secretary and 
four members of the National Electoral Committee (OVB). 
  Deputy Interior State Secretary Pal Kara became OVB 
secretary. Members are Arpad Erdei, Hungarian Lawyers' general 
secretary, Sandor Horvath, Independent Lawyers' Forum 
vice-president, Istvan Kukorelli, dean of constitutional law at 
Budapest Eotvos Lorand University, and Janos Nemeth, Eotvos 
general deputy rector. 
  In keeping with the Hungarian-U.S. inter-governmental 
agreement on intellectual property rights, Parliament today 
amended a 1969 law, bringing it into line with European 
legislation. A draft resolution was adopted to join the 1961 
Rome Convention protecting performing artists, audio record 
manufacturers, and broadcasters. 
  Changes concern rights of both authors and performers, as 
well as the patents system. Earlier legislation covering 
chemical, food, and pharmaceutical products protected the 
manufacturing process, while now the product itself will enjoy 
legal protection. 

</TEXT>

