<H4>   Talks With Pawlak Reported </H4>
<F P=102> LD0702212594 Warsaw PAP in English 2107 GMT 7 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0702212594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, Feb 7 -- Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak on 
Monday received Russian Interior Minister Viktor Yerin. The 
meeting was attended by Interior Minister Andrzej Milczanowski, 
the government press office announced. 
  The talks focused on cooperation between Polish and Russian 
Interior Ministries which had resulted in some improvement in 
effectiveness of fighting crime. The two sides stressed the 
need to share experiences in the field of tactics and techniques 
used by police in Poland and Russia, the communique of the press 
office reads. 

