<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Egyutteles Movement Warns of `Open Dictatorship' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0702151094 Prague CTK in English 1510 GMT 5 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0702151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Feb 5 (CTK) -- Egyutteles 
(Co-existence), a Hungarian minority movement in Slovakia, warns 
against "the installation of an open dictatorship" in connection 
with the current stalemate in parliament. 
  In a statement issued by the Egyutteles Parliamentary Group 
and given to CTK today, movement representatives said they 
considered the constant questioning of the legitimacy of 
parliament to be part of a dangerous scenario which could 
develop into establishing an open dictatorship. 
  The opposition movement voices the view that the current 
Slovak Government was incapable of stopping the economic fall of 
society and of finding a way out of the accumulated tension. By 
the lack of will to create a functioning government coalition 
the ruling Movement for a Democratic Slovakia (HZDS) could 
create a permanent governmental and parliamentary crisis. The 
government lacks a concept for the transformation of society and 
a strategy of economic and social policy. That is why it is 
resorting to ever more arrogant methods to maintain and 
concentrate power, the statement says. 

</TEXT>

