<F P=101> Slovakia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Agreement Signed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902150794 Prague CTK in English 2134 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0902150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague, Feb 8 (CTK) -- Slovak and German Defense 
Ministers Volker Ruhe and Imrich Andrejcak signed an agreement 
on military cooperation between the countries. 
  This year 25 joint operations on the territory of the two 
states will take place, Ruhe told journalists. "Usually this 
sort of event is staged only in the second or third year of 
cooperation. This illustrates the accelerated contacts between 
the two countries' armed forces," he added. 
  The ministers are proposing an exchange of experts, not 
units 
or joint maneuvers. The general staffs are to discuss the 
exchange of units, Andrejcak said. Ruhe said that Slovak and 
German troops would probably first meet in Poland to where they 
had been invited. 
  The Slovak Army will consult Bundeswehr experts regarding 
the 
creation of a task force brigade. 

</TEXT>

