<H3> <TI>   Serbian Police Close Albanian Shops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0802165694 Tirana ATA in English 1102 GMT 6 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU0802165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana ATA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tirana, February 6 (ATA) -- Serbian financial 
police has recently undertaken an extensive control which is 
mostly aimed at the Albanian traders, who are not only fined 
with large sums of money but they are also forced to close down 
their shops. 
  Serbian civil policemen provoked Albanian traders and under 
the pretext of non-observation of new monetary measures to help 
dinar which is going bankrupt, order the closure of their shops. 
As a result of these measures, 35 shops have been closed until 
now in Mitrovice, five in Serbice. During the past 15 days 
alone, the daily Serbian newspaper JEDINSTVO, published in 
Prishtina, writes 70 Albanian private shops have been closed in 
the regions which are called "Circle of Kosova." 

</TEXT>

