<F P=100> BULGARIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Survives No-Confidence Vote </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902152894 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1510 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0902152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Sofia Khorizont Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Bulgarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] We switch to the National Assembly Hall, where the 
results of the no-confidence vote will be announced. National 
Assembly Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov is giving the floor to 
Khristo Markov, who will announce the results: 
  [Markov] Today, 9 February, the National Assembly conducted 
a secret vote on the proposal to vote on confidence in the 
cabinet in connection with the failure of the cabinet to 
implement its duties regarding the citizens' security and the 
public law and order. The no-confidence vote was proposed on 28 
January by the parliamentary faction of the Union of Democratic 
Forces [SDS]. 
  A commission composed by Khristo Markov, Ruslan Semerdzhiev, 
Mariela Miteva, and Kiril Zhelev announces the following results 
of the no-confidence vote: 
  Some 228 National Assembly members took part in the vote. 
Some 89 ballots were cast in support of the no-confidence vote. 
Some 135 ballots were cast against the no-confidence proposal. 
Three envelopes were found empty, and one contained more than 
one ballot. 
  On the basis of the voting results, and on Article 81, 
Paragraphs 1 and 2 of the Bulgarian Constitution, and Paragraph 
4 of the additional instructions on the activity of the National 
Assembly, the no-confidence vote in the cabinet has been 
rejected. 

</TEXT>

