<F P=100> HUNGARY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hungary, Ukraine To Cooperate in `Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0802150894 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 
1400 GMT 8 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0802150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Budapest Kossuth Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hungarian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hungary and Ukraine will cooperate in the 
Partnership for Peace program. The defense ministers of the two 
countries have agreed on this at their meeting in Budapest. 
  Army General Vitaliy Hryhororovich Radetskyy, speaking at a 
press briefing, said that they also discussed regional 
cooperation from which they do not want to exclude Russia. They 
also decided that a committee of experts would be set up to 
examine the possibility of military industrial cooperation. 
Hungary is interested primarily in obtaining parts for 
aircraft, tanks, and armored combat vehicles. 

</TEXT>

