<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Germany's Ruehe Visits, Comments on NATO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902211394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1958 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0902211394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prague (DDP/ADN) -- Defense Minister Volker Ruehe 
sees "certain possibilities" that Slovakia could accede to NATO 
by the end of the century. Ruehe said at the conclusion of a 
two-day visit to Bratislava (Pressburg) that this is, however, 
dependent on international developments. The German delegation 
has gained the impression that Slovakia is preparing for 
membership of western structures in all areas. 
  In Bratislava, Ruehe met President Kovac, Prime Minister 
Meciar, Assembly Speaker Gasparovic, Foreign Minister Moravcik, 
and his counterpart Andrejcak. An agreement on cooperation in 
the military field was signed during the visit. Ruehe said that 
he sees the preconditions for close, positive cooperation 
between Germany and Slovakia. 

</TEXT>

