<F P=100> YUGOSLAVIA </F>
<F P=101> Serbia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Milosevic, Draskovic on Parliament Delay </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902204094 Belgrade RTB Television Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1830 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0902204094 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade RTB Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As we have learned, Serbian President Slobodan 
Milosevic met with Vuk Draskovic, leader of the Serbian Renewal 
Movement [SPO] today. Let us hear what Vuk Draskovic stated to 
POLITIKA Television after the meeting with President Milosevic: 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] You were with 
President Milosevic. Can you tell us what you discussed? 
  [Draskovic] We discussed the reasons for the delay in the 
formation of the parliament, which is a peculiar form of 
obstruction. I informed the president of the fact that this 
obstruction cannot be overcome without a political agreement. 
To the president's words that he favored a government of 
national unity, I replied that, regarding the SPO and DEPOS 
[Democratic Movement of Serbia], we want more than that; 
national unity. However, in this, the SPO, naturally, wishes to 
carry some of the responsibility for the atmosphere in the 
parliamentary life of the country -- Serbia and the federal 
state. Regarding government, we do not wish to take part in any 
government, be it republican or federal, and this was my stance. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

