<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spiroiu Denies Removal of 4th Army Commander </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902122694 Bucharest Radio Romania Network in Romanian 
0900 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0902122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest Radio Romania Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In an interview granted today to one of our 
correspondents, Lieutenant General Niculae Spiroiu, Romanian 
national defense minister, said that he, together with other top 
officials of the ministry, had examined in Cluj the 1993 balance 
of the 4th Army [the Transylvanian army], as well as aspects 
related to military discipline and order in that army. They 
found that the activity of the 4th Army was very well organized. 
  Minister Spiroiu rejected allegations published in today's 
edition of the daily ULTIMUL CUVANT [THE LAST WORD] that he went 
to Cluj to remove the current commander of the 4th Army, General 
Paul Cheler. Spiroiu added that he regrets that such news is 
being circulated without first checking with the Army Press 
Office. 

</TEXT>

