<F P=100> ROMANIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spiroiu Wants To End Conflict With Tudor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1002104994 Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA in Romanian 8 Feb 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1002104994 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMANIA LIBERA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Romanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "General Spiroiu Wants To End </F>
Conflict With C.V. Tudor"] 
  [Text] Romania's minister of national defense, General 
Niculae Spiroiu, declared in a television broadcast of the "Pro 
Patria" program that he wishes to end the conflict with Senator 
C.V. Tudor. "Let us consider it a closed chapter, we have much 
to do in the Army," said Mr. Spiroiu, although at the news 
conference of the Greater Romania Party on 3 February the leader 
of that party continued his accusations and slander against the 
dignitary, who is a member of the Vacaroiu government. He 
called the defense minister: "A minister who is a trafficker and 
a maniac," "a political adventurer," "the epitome of 
incompetence," and a person who "demolished the arms industry," 
"turned the ministry into a small feudal family," and 
"permanently misinformed the state institutions." Here are a 
few examples of the way Senator V.C. Tudor portrayed Minister 
Spiroiu at the recent news conference of the Greater Romania 
Party. Therefore, the general's decision to call for an end to 
the conflict is viewed as a more than surprising act, since Mr. 
Spiroiu has not even turned to the legal authorities to have 
Senator C.V. Tudor reprimanded for his remarks. 

</TEXT>

