<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Stages Mass Demonstration in Warsaw </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902174494 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1700 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902174494 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A demonstration by Solidarity took place in Warsaw 
today, in protest against price increases, falling workers' 
incomes, and the increase of the number of unemployed. Changes 
in the budget for this year were demanded. 
  In a speech made before the office of the Council of 
Ministers, Union Chairman Marian Krzaklewski demanded the 
adoption by 15 March this year of the laws comprising the pact 
on the state enterprise. He announced that there will be further 
demonstrations if this is not done. Over and above that, he 
said that Solidarity is preparing its own draft constitution, 
one that is representativeof the entire independence-oriented 
and Solidarity sector. 
  The participants in the demonstration delivered petitions 
into the hands of Deputy Sejm Speaker Jozef Zych and Council of 
Ministers Office Head Michal Strak. In the petitions the trade 
unionists are demanding changes in the budget for this year that 
would allow for a decrease in the growing negative economic and 
social phenomena. 
  The participants in the demonstration included Jan 
Olszewski, 
Jan Parys, Adam Glapinski, and also groups from the Movement for 
the Republic and the Third Republic Movement. According to the 
police controlling traffic, around 30,000 people took part in 
the demonstration, and according to Marian Kraklewski around 
100,000. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-30922 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu028_p_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-028 </AU>
