<F P=100> BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Serb-Muslim Cease-Fire Agreed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902202794 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in 
Serbo-Croatian 1949 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902202794 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sarajevo, 9 Feb (TANJUG) -- Major General Manoljo 
Milovanovic, chief of the general staff of the army of the 
Srpska republic, stated this evening that a cease-fire coming 
into effect at noon tomorrow [10 February] was agreed at a 
meeting between Serb and Muslim military representatives this 
afternoon, with the mediation of General Michael Rose, UN 
Protection Forces [UNPROFOR] commander for Bosnia-Herzegovina. 
  General Milovanovic said that an agreement was reached to 
place both Serb and Muslim artillery under UNPROFOR control for 
the duration of the cease-fire. 
  He explained that UNPROFOR has conveyed to the Muslim side 
the Serb side's proposal regarding the cease-fire and the 
setting up of a mixed military commission which will find ways 
to maintain the cease-fire. He added that the Muslim side has 
agreed to this. 
  The cease-fire will be guaranteed by UNPROFOR. Commissions 
will tour the entire front around Sarajevo in order to establish 
where these sensitive spots are and deploy UNPROFOR observers 
there to determine who is violating the truce, General 
Milovanovic stressed. 
  The chief of staff said he was surprised by General Rose's 
claim that some kind of an agreement was signed at today's 
meeting. He specified that nothing was signed and that all that 
was accomplished was a verbal agreement, whose details he cited. 
He emphasized that this is a truce and that the Muslim 
artillery is in no way exempt from it. 
  General Milovanovic added that UNPROFOR and the Serb and 
Muslim sides have assumed responsibility for inspecting all 
positions through mixed military commissions and devising ways 
to maintain the truce. These ways will be discussed tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-30925 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu028_i_94004" </HT>


