<H3> <TI>   UNHCR Orders Staff To Leave Banja Luka </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU0902151594 Belgrade Radio Beograd Network in 
Serbo-Croatian 1400 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU0902151594 </F>
<F P=104>  Belgrade Radio Beograd Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The staff of the Banja Luka UNHCR office today left 
the town. We received this piece of information a few minutes 
ago. 
  The head of the office, Fridrich Rotwate, informed Mayor 
Predrag Radic that he had received the order from New York. He 
said that he did not have any other details, or did not want to 
give them. The residents of Banja Luka who are working as 
haulage operators and drivers or are performing other jobs in 
that organization have stayed behind. 
  The officials of the International Red Cross stayed in Banja 
Luka and are performing their duties. Their head, Christian 
Brunner, told the mayor that they do not have plans at present 
to leave the town. 

</TEXT>

