<F P=100> CZECH REPUBLIC </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Decides To Participate in `Partnership' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902164894 Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network in Czech 1600 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902164894 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague Radiozurnal Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Czech </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet is in session in Prague today. Jitka 
Kucerova phoned in this report. 
  [Kucerova] The cabinet has decided on the participation of 
the Czech Republic in the Partnership for Peace program. The 
so-called presentation document will be submitted by 31 March. 
The individual program of the Czech Republic in this project 
will be worked out on its basis. 
  The government also discussed the situation of national 
minorities. Vaclav Klaus said the following on this question: 
Our point of departure is no discrimination against minorities. 
The government, however, does not intend to set up any special 
institution to discuss these problems. 
  A draft amendment to the law on land communications was also 
adopted. In practice, this will mean the introduction of the 
long-discussed motorway tax. The preliminary day of 
introduction is 1 January 1995. 

</TEXT>

