<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Butrus-Ghali Authorizes Defensive Air Strikes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1102171494 Paris AFP in English 1706 GMT 11 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1102171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] United Nations, Feb 11 (AFP) -- UN Secretary General 
Butrus Butrus-Ghali has authorized his representative in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina to approve the use of air strikes to defend 
UN personnel anywhere in the former Yugoslav republic. 
  The representative, Yasushi Akashi, already had the 
authority 
to call in air support to help operations aimed at reopening the 
airport at Tuzla and for rotating UN personnel in and out of the 
besieged areas of Srebenica and Zepa. 
  Butrus-Ghali's authorization was notified Friday [11 
February] in a letter to the UN Security Council and which was 
obtained by AFP. 

</TEXT>

