<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks on Bosnia Peace Continue in Geneva </TI></H3>
<H4>   Karadzic Threatens To Secede </H4>
<F P=102> LD1302094794 Bern Swiss Radio International in English 0900 
GMT 13 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1302094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern Swiss Radio International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The ethnic Serbian leader says ethnic Serbians will 
unilaterally secede with territory they hold if the Muslims 
continue to reject the latest map dividing Bosnia into three 
states. Radovan Karadzic made the statement after peace talks 
in Geneva ended in deadlock on Saturday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

