<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   End of Strike Denied </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1202101994 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 0700 
GMT 12 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1202101994 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The TV "Wiadomosci" and "Panorama" programs carried 
reports yesterday on the signing of an accord between the board 
of the Jastrzebie Coal Company [JSW] and the Trade Union of 
Miners of Poland [ZZGwP], which was to end the strike at the 
seven mines of this company. Unfortunately, the miners at these 
mines are still on strike. 
  Meanwhile, as Romuald Boszko, press spokesman of the protest 
staff at the JSW, has reported, the signing of this accord has 
no significance with regard to the course of the strike. The 
strike is directed, the press spokesman stressed, by the protest 
staff, the composition of which does not include the ZZGwP. The 
protest staff, on the other hand, does include three other trade 
unions: Kontra, Solidarity, and Solidarity '80. The dispatcher 
at the State Hard Coal Agency in Katowice has confirmed that the 
work forces have not commenced work at any of the JSW mines. 
  Beginning at 1500 today, additional talks will take place 
with the protesting miners at the provisional headquarters of 
the JSW. As we discovered at the board of the company, a 
consensus has been reached on 95 percent of the proposals. 
There is still a lack of accord with regard to compensation for 
the time spent on strike. 

</TEXT>

