<F P=100> POLAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   IMF Conditions Fulfilled for Debt Reduction </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0902192294 Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network in Polish 1800 
GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0902192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw Radio Warszawa Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Polish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to initial data for 1994, Poland has 
fulfilled the standby agreement reached in November 1992 with 
the IMF. The fulfillment of this agreement is a condition for a 
20-percent reduction--that is. about $8 billion in government 
debts to the states who are our creditors grouped in the Paris 
Club. The club is to make a decision on this matter at the 
beginning of April. 

</TEXT>

