<F P=102>  AU1002151894 Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network in Slovene 
1800 GMT 9 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1002151894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ljubljana Radio Slovenia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovene </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This evening, the prime minister's cabinet reported 
that U.S. Ambassador Alan Wendt was received by Prime Minister 
Dr. Janez Drnovsek today. 
  The prime minister praised highly the accomplished level of 
cooperation in the political and economic spheres and at the 
same time informed Mr. Wendt that our government today explained 
its cooperation and contacts with the U.S. diplomatic mission in 
Ljubljana to the public. 
  Ambassador Wendt emphasized that a clear stance of the 
Slovene Government is very important for further strengthening 
of relations between the states and especially for the support 
of the United States for Slovenia's integration in international 
political and economic institutions. 

