<F P=100> SLOVAKIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Program Statement of HZDS Deputies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1002225294 Bratislava STV 1 Television Network in Slovak 
2100 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1002225294 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava STV 1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press agency of the Slovak Republic has 
succeeded in obtaining a program statement by the signatories of 
the Alternative of Political Realism within the Movement for a 
Democratic Slovakia [HZDS]. The signatories gave a briefing on 
their initiative to members and deputies of the ruling movement 
at today's session of the HZDS deputies' club in Casta 
Papiernicka. We quote: 
  Being aware of the fact that a confrontational policy does 
not guarantee Slovakia's further positive development and that 
it is necessary to concentrate the efforts and responsibilities 
of political forces toward overcoming problems Slovakia has been 
struggling against, taking into account the inevitability of a 
political reconciliation in the period preceeding early 
elections, we propose: 
  1. To form a government with the participation of the HZDS, 
the Party of the Democratic Left, the Christian Democratic 
Movement, the Slovak National Party, and the Alliance of 
Democrats--without personal participation of the chairmen of 
those parties and movements. 
  2. To invite experts without party affiliation to join the 
government. 
  We consider it inevitable to return to the movement's 
original democratic principles and to fulfill its liberal social 
program. 
  With the aim of following these aims, we have created the 
Alternative of Political Realism within the HZDS. 

</TEXT>

