<H3> <TI>   HZDS Deputies' Proposal on New Government </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1002212694 Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1002212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Bratislava Rozhlasova Stanica Slovensko Network 
in Slovak 2030 GMT 10 Feb 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Slovak </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The press agency of the Slovak Republic has issued a 
program statement by the signatories of the Alternative of 
Political Realism within the Movement for a Democratic Slovakia 
[HZDS]. The signatories gave a briefing on their initiative to 
members and deputies of the ruling movement at today's session 
of the HZDS deputies' club in Casta Papiernicka. 
  They propose to form a government with the participation of 
the HZDS, the Party of the Democratic Left, the Christian 
Democratic Movement, the Slovak National Party, and the Alliance 
of Democrats--without personal participation of the chairmen of 
the parties and movements in question. They also propose to 
invite experts without party affiliation to join the government. 
  The statement issued by the Alternative of Political Realism 
says that its signatories consider it inevitable to return to 
the original democratic principles. 
  This text was signed by 10 HZDS parliament deputies. The 
Alternative was formed within the framework of the HZDS. 

</TEXT>

