<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Serbo-Croatian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] General Ratko Mladic, the commander of Serb 
formations in Bosnia-Herzegovina, had a meeting yesterday in 
Drvar, at his own request, with General Jean Cot, the UNPROFOR 
[UN Protection Forces] commander for the former Yugoslavia, the 
Zagreb heaquarters of UNPROFOR announced today. 
  Mladic has agreed to meet with General Rasim Delic, the 
commander of the Muslim forces, on Tuesday 15 February at 
Sarajevo Airport, the statement says. The aim of this meeting 
is to continue, and flesh out, the concrete measures to ensure 
the success of the cease-fire, which is already being 
implemented in and around Sarajevo. This means collecting up and 
withdrawing heavy weaponry and reducing forces on front lines, a 
statement issued by UNPROFOR's public relations office says. 

