<F P=106> [Report by Mirza Sadikovic from Bihac] </F>
  [Text] Karadzic's deadline for his butchers to enter Bihac 
-- to capture the right bank of the Una River, that is -- runs 
out today at noon. That is why his bloodthirsty butchers spent 
the entire night charging and attacking at all the defense 
lines. They attacked the Grmusko-Srbljanski Plateau, Hasin Vrh, 
Grabez. In many of these places hand-to-hand fighting 
continues. Bad weather conditions are not deterring the Chetnik 
artillery from further destroying civilian buildings, destroying 
Bihac, [word indistinct], suburban districts, and Cazin. 
  [Words indistinct] that Fikret Abdic yesterday sent to 
Tudjman, Karadzic, Milosevic, Boban, and his other superiors, to 
urgently help his so-called army defend itself against the 5th 
Corps. Obviously, (?he too) fears the growing awareness of the 
people of Velika Kladusa. 
  This has been Mirza Sadikovic reporting for Radio Television 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

